{
  "texts": [
    "Data FabricData fabric [23][24][25] focuses on centralization and unified data access.",
    "It creates a unified data integration layer by connecting existing data systems and components to provide a single source of truth for data, similar to the purpose of master data management [26].",
    "It avoids the traditional problems of centralized systems by connecting data from different sources rather than moving the data itself to centralized storage.",
    "As a centralized architecture, data fabric simplifies data access, governance, standardization, and quality assurance.Data fabric is ideal for enterprises with interwind business domains or that require a single source of truth for data.",
    "However, the centralized nature of the data fabric may result in potential bottlenecks, slower responsiveness to domainspecific needs, dependency on a centralized team, and scalability challenges."
  ]
}